BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: A rival enterprise in a struggle for advantage over the subject enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: A rival enterprise in a struggle for advantage over the subject enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Competitor

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: A role played by an individual or enterprise that has investigated, ordered, received, or paid for products or services from the subject enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: A role played by an individual or enterprise that has investigated, ordered, received, or paid for products or services from the subject enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Customer

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: The aggregate of surrounding conditions or Influencers affecting the existence or development of an enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: The aggregate of surrounding conditions or Influencers affecting the existence or development of an enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Environment

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: An enterprise that shares risks and profit with the subject enterprise (or is associated with the subject enterprise to share risks and profit) because this is mutually beneficial.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: An enterprise that shares risks and profit with the subject enterprise (or is associated with the subject enterprise to share risks and profit) because this is mutually beneficial.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Partner

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: An order prescribed by an authority such as a government body or the management of an enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: An order prescribed by an authority such as a government body or the management of an enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Regulation

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: A role played by an individual or enterprise that can furnish or provide products or services to the subject enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: A role played by an individual or enterprise that can furnish or provide products or services to the subject enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Supplier

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: The role of technology, including its developments and limitations — there may be prerequisites for use of technology; there may be enterprise activity that technology enables or restricts.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: The role of technology, including its developments and limitations — there may be prerequisites for use of technology; there may be enterprise activity that technology enables or restricts.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Technology

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: Something that is taken for granted or without proof.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: Something that is taken for granted or without proof.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Assumption

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: Value An ideal, custom, or institution that an enterprise promotes or agrees with (either positive or negative).
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: Value An ideal, custom, or institution that an enterprise promotes or agrees with (either positive or negative).
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Corporate

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: A Corporate Value explicitly set forth and declared.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: A Corporate Value explicitly set forth and declared.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Explicit Value

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: A Corporate Value not explicitly declared but nonetheless understood by some or all of the people in an enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: A Corporate Value not explicitly declared but nonetheless understood by some or all of the people in an enterprise.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Implicit Value

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: The basic underlying framework or features of a system.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation_plain: The basic underlying framework or features of a system.
BMMInfluencerCategory.Name: Infrastructure

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: A point in question or a matter that is in dispute as between contending partners.

BMMInfluencerCategory.Documentation: Prerogative A right or privilege exercised by virtue of ownership or position in an enterprise.

Operation.Documentation:
Initiates and starts a sessions with one or more DW1000. If rst is not set or value 0xff, a soft resets (i.e. command triggered) are used and it is assumed that no reset line is wired.

irqThe interrupt line/pin that connects the Arduino. rstThe reset line/pin for hard resets of ICs that connect to the Arduino. Value 0xff means soft reset.
Operation.Documentation_plain: Initiates and starts a sessions with one or more DW1000. If rst is not set or value 0xff, a soft resets (i.e. command triggered) are used and it is assumed that no reset line is wired. irqThe interrupt line/pin that connects the Arduino. rstThe reset line/pin for hard resets of ICs that connect to the Arduino. Value 0xff means soft reset.
Operation.Name: begin

Parameter.Documentation: The interrupt line/pin that connects the Arduino.
Parameter.Documentation_plain: The interrupt line/pin that connects the Arduino.
Parameter.Name: irq

Parameter.Documentation: The reset line/pin for hard resets of ICs that connect to the Arduino. Value 0xff means soft reset.
Parameter.Documentation_plain: The reset line/pin for hard resets of ICs that connect to the Arduino. Value 0xff means soft reset.
Parameter.Name: rst

Operation.Documentation:
Selects a specific DW1000 chip for communication. In case of a single DW1000 chip in use this call only needs to be done once at start up, but is still mandatory. Other than a call to reselect() this function performs an initial setup of the now-selected chip.

ssThe chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Operation.Documentation_plain: Selects a specific DW1000 chip for communication. In case of a single DW1000 chip in use this call only needs to be done once at start up, but is still mandatory. Other than a call to reselect() this function performs an initial setup of the now-selected chip. ssThe chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Operation.Name: select

Parameter.Documentation: The chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Parameter.Documentation_plain: The chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Parameter.Name: ss

Operation.Documentation:
(Re-)selects a specific DW1000 chip for communication. In case of a single DW1000 chip in use this call is not needed; only a call to select() has to be performed once at start up. Other than a call to select() this function does not perform an initial setup of the (again-)selected chips and assumes it to have a valid configuration loaded.

ssThe chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Operation.Documentation_plain: (Re-)selects a specific DW1000 chip for communication. In case of a single DW1000 chip in use this call is not needed; only a call to select() has to be performed once at start up. Other than a call to select() this function does not perform an initial setup of the (again-)selected chips and assumes it to have a valid configuration loaded. ssThe chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Operation.Name: reselect

Parameter.Documentation: The chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Parameter.Documentation_plain: The chip select line/pin that connects the to-be-selected chip with the Arduino.
Parameter.Name: ss

Operation.Documentation:
Specifies whether to suppress any frame check measures while sending or receiving messages. If suppressed, no 2-byte checksum is appended to the message before sending and this checksum is also not expected at receiver side. Note that when suppressing frame checks, the error event handler (attached via attachReceiveErrorHandler()) will not be triggered if received data is corrupted.

Frame checks are enabled as part of setDefaults() if the device is in idle mode.

valtrue to suppress frame check on sender and receiver side, false otherwise.
Operation.Documentation_plain: Specifies whether to suppress any frame check measures while sending or receiving messages. If suppressed, no 2-byte checksum is appended to the message before sending and this checksum is also not expected at receiver side. Note that when suppressing frame checks, the error event handler (attached via attachReceiveErrorHandler()) will not be triggered if received data is corrupted. Frame checks are enabled as part of setDefaults() if the device is in idle mode. valtrue to suppress frame check on sender and receiver side, false otherwise.
Operation.Name: suppressFrameCheck

Parameter.Documentation: true to suppress frame check on sender and receiver side, false otherwise.
Parameter.Documentation_plain: true to suppress frame check on sender and receiver side, false otherwise.
Parameter.Name: val

Operation.Documentation:
Specifies the data transmission rate of the DW1000 chip. One of the valuesTRX_RATE_110KBPS (i.e. 110 kb/s)TRX_RATE_850KBPS (i.e. 850 kb/s)TRX_RATE_6800KBPS (i.e. 6.8 Mb/s) has to be provided.

See setDefaults() and enableMode() for additional information on data rate settings.

rateThe data transmission rate, encoded by the above defined constants.
Operation.Documentation_plain: Specifies the data transmission rate of the DW1000 chip. One of the valuesTRX_RATE_110KBPS (i.e. 110 kb/s)TRX_RATE_850KBPS (i.e. 850 kb/s)TRX_RATE_6800KBPS (i.e. 6.8 Mb/s) has to be provided. See setDefaults() and enableMode() for additional information on data rate settings. rateThe data transmission rate, encoded by the above defined constants.

Operation.Documentation:
Specifies the pulse repetition frequency (PRF) of data transmissions with the DW1000. EitherTX_PULSE_FREQ_16MHZ (i.e. 16 MHz)TX_PULSE_FREQ_64MHZ (i.e. 64 MHz) has to be chosen.

Note that the 16 MHz setting is more power efficient, while the 64 MHz setting requires more power, but also delivers slightly better transmission performance (i.e. on communication range and timestamp accuracy) (see DWM1000 User Manual, section 9.3).

See setDefaults() and enableMode() for additional information on PRF settings.

Operation.Documentation:
Specifies the mode of operation for the DW1000. Modes of operation are pre-defined combinations of data rate, pulse repetition frequency, preamble and channel settings that properly go together. If you simply want the chips to work, choosing a mode is preferred over manual configuration.

The following modes are pre-configured and one of them needs to be chosen:MODE_LONGDATA_RANGE_LOWPOWER (basically this is 110 kb/s data rate, 16 MHz PRF and long preambles)MODE_SHORTDATA_FAST_LOWPOWER (basically this is 6.8 Mb/s data rate, 16 MHz PRF and short preambles)MODE_LONGDATA_FAST_LOWPOWER (basically this is 6.8 Mb/s data rate, 16 MHz PRF and long preambles)MODE_SHORTDATA_FAST_ACCURACY (basically this is 6.8 Mb/s data rate, 64 MHz PRF and short preambles)MODE_LONGDATA_FAST_ACCURACY (basically this is 6.8 Mb/s data rate, 64 MHz PRF and long preambles)MODE_LONGDATA_RANGE_ACCURACY (basically this is 110 kb/s data rate, 64 MHz PRF and long preambles)

Note that LOWPOWER and ACCURACY refers to the better power efficiency and improved transmission performance of 16 MHZ and 64 MHZ PRF respectively (see setPulseFrequency()).

The default setting that is selected by setDefaults() is MODE_LONGDATA_RANGE_LOWPOWER.
